<!-- ============ FAQ ============ -->
<section class="section" style="padding-bottom: 80px;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Frequently Asked Questions</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Everything you need to know.</h2>
    </div>
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          How does Teamwork Commerce achieve 99.9% inventory accuracy?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Through the industry's only native end-to-end RFID stack. RFID-powered cycle counts scan thousands of items in minutes without pulling product off racks. Real-time reconciliation updates global stock levels instantly. Combined with anomaly detection that flags suspicious inventory movement, this eliminates ghost SKUs and delivers 99.9% accuracy across all locations.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          Can cycle counts be done without closing the store?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Rolling RFID cycle counts run during business hours without disrupting operations. Associates scan with the iOS device while customers shop. A typical 10-store chain recovers $150,000–$300,000 in previously "lost" stock within the first 12 months of switching to weekly RFID counts.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          How does stock-out prevention work?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>The system monitors the velocity of RFID tags moving through the sales floor. When a SKU is approaching zero at a location, it queues a transfer from the nearest warehouse or store with surplus stock, and can trigger vendor re-orders. Demand forecasting operates at the SKU-and-location level with up to 95% accuracy.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          How does Teamwork Commerce inventory compare to New Black EVA and NewStore?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>New Black and NewStore offer unified commerce inventory but require third-party middleware for deep RFID workflows. Teamwork Commerce is the only platform with native end-to-end RFID — from source tagging through checkout. This means cycle counts, receiving, loss prevention, and real-time tracking all run on one system with no integration points to break. The result: 99.9% accuracy vs. the industry average of 70–80%.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          Does the system work offline?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Store-and-Forward technology keeps all inventory operations running during network outages. Receiving, counts, adjustments, and transfers continue on the iOS device. Data is encrypted locally and syncs automatically when connectivity returns — zero data gaps, zero downtime.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

